         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">P.S. ¶  Please note remarks within. ¶ C/o Messr Canning &amp; Sinclair ¶ Stock &amp; Station Agents ¶ St Georges Terrace Perth W.A. ¶ 12 Augt 1891...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">91.08.12a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From R. Moore McNeece</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M1, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">P.S.</hi>
               </seg> Please note remarks within.<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, 'Segoe UI Symbol'; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">This refers to remarks presented here as postscripts, which are written, along with the address, on the inside of the folded sheet, while the text of the letter is on the outside of the sheet. McNeece has not been further identified.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">C/o Messr Canning &amp; Sinclair</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Stock &amp; Station Agents</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">St Georges Terrace Perth W.A.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">12 Augt 1891</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">The Baron Von Muëller KCMG &amp;c</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne Victoria</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear Sir,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Upon my return from the north, I received your kind letter<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, 'Segoe UI Symbol'; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Letter not found.</p>
               </note> also parcel of fodder grass, which I gave to Mr E Keane to experiment in his Estate at Mt Barker in the Southern line of Railway.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>With reference to the Sea weed and shells I hope to get you a supply from a gentleman connected with the Pearling Industry I regret my business did not take me to Champion Bay<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, 'Segoe UI Symbol'; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">WA.</p>
               </note> or I should have made it my special business to have secured some for you.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am busy on the Helena Estate eradicating the "<seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">York Road poison plant</hi>
               </seg>" with Chinese and Boys. It is a Herculean Task. It requires to be taken out root and branch as every fibre exposed to the atmosphere will it is said shoot. Burning it does not good — regrowth thicker than ever. Fibre and leaf enclosed what is your opinion as to killing it? Can you suggest a modus operandi? — other than taking it out root and branch like briar then burning it as it dries. It is deadly as you know to stock particularly when in flower in spring. Kindly give me the benefit of your sage experience.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">With regards and and wishing you hale and hearty</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>&amp; am, Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>yours very truly</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>R. Moore McNeece.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 12pt; text-align: center; "
               xml:lang="en">Remarks re plant.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">The plant as you know has a thick butt, in fine soil the roots extend to a great length, having many fibrous roots</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">York road poison</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>there are two species one which grows like spear grass, but is only deadly when in flower.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">RMcN</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Address</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Mr R. Moore McNeece</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>C/o Messrs Canning &amp; Sinclair</p>
